     Phase 4: Long-Term SEO Optimization (Week 2+)

     Goal

     Implement pre-rendering to improve search engine indexing reliability.

     Problem Statement

     Current Issue: React SPA with Client-Side Rendering (CSR)
     - Search engines receive empty HTML: <div id="root"></div>
     - Meta tags added by react-helmet-async AFTER page load
     - Content not available until JavaScript executes
     - Googlebot has limited JS rendering budget
     - Bing, DuckDuckGo have poor JS rendering support

     Evidence:
     - View source on /events/:id shows generic meta tags
     - Structured data not in initial HTML
     - Content requires JavaScript to render

     ---
     Solution Options Analysis

     Option 1: Vite Pre-rendering Plugin (RECOMMENDED - Quick)

     Pros:
     - Fastest implementation (2-4 hours)
     - Keeps current architecture
     - Works with existing Vite build
     - No breaking changes
     - Pre-renders at build time

     Cons:
     - Static generation only (not true SSR)
     - Need to rebuild for content updates
     - Limited to known routes

     Estimated Effort: 2-4 hours
     Cost: Free

